<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-09T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-09T17:00:00-05:00" n="1498" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1498">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The</hi>
                            <gloss type="from">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                            <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-09T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 9, 1915, 5 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2088. Your 2736, September 3. Is Department to understand that British
                            Government has agreed to and officially sanctioned the use of these
                            German ships interned in the United States and other neutral ports?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>